---
title: Seared Serrano Steak with Sweet Mango Slaw & Cilantro Rice
description: A mix of balsamic vinegar, garlic, and serrano pepper makes for a sweet, spicy, and tangy steak marinade. For a hit of brightness, we’ve paired juicy mango with red onion and lime for subtly sweet side slaw. Classic cilantro-lime rice is the perfect base to soak up all those flavors!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/55709cc34dab7130718b4568.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/55709cc34dab7130718b4568.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 497 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 5 g
cuisine: Fusion
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/seared-serrano-steak-55709cc34dab7130718b4568
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}. Dice the remaining half
onion. In a #small pot{}, heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} over medium heat.
Add the diced onion and cook, tossing, ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add
the @basmati rice{3/4%cup} to the pot and toss to coat, then add
@water{1 1/2%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} to the pot. Bring to a boil,
cover, and reduce to a simmer for ~{15%minutes}, until rice is tender.

Meanwhile, peel the @mango{1}, then slice the fruit around the flat pit. Cut
mango pieces into thin matchsticks. Zest and juice the @lime{1}. Chop the
@cilantro{1%bunch} stems and leaves, keeping both separate. Mince the
@garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Mince the @serrano pepper{1}(minced), removing the
ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat.

Make the marinade: in a #shallow dish{}, combine @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoons},
the @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}, garlic, add up to half the minced serrano
pepper, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @flank steak{12%ounce}
to the dish and flip to coat in the marinade. Season with salt and pepper.

> If you have extra time, let the steak marinate for longer.

Make the mango slaw: toss the mango, cilantro stems, sliced red onion (to taste),
and half the lime zest in a #medium bowl{} with the lime juice. Add the
remaining serrano pepper.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the steak and cook
~{4-5%minutes} per side, until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest
for ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice against the grain.

Stir the cilantro leaves and remaining lime zest into the rice.

Plate the cilantro rice, then top with the sliced steak and mango slaw. Enjoy!